•	Enabling the Company and its employees to contact one another using an employee’s work telephone, e-mail address or physical mailing address;

•	Enabling the Company and its employees to contact External Parties using work telephone, e-mail address or physical mailing address;

•	Assisting with the Company’s legal, compliance and auditing functions; 

•	Investigating reports of alleged misconduct or similar concern made via the Company’s 24-hour, toll-free employee hotline or through another method of reporting; or

•	Ordinary business reasons, which includes the evaluation of products and services and related issues. 

	Purposes For Sensitive Personal Information

•	Protecting the vital interests of the European employee or another person;

•	Necessary for establishing legal claims or defenses;

•	Required to provide medical care or diagnosis; or

•	Enabling the Company to fulfill its employment law obligations.
